author: cbs8
title: Authorities probe grass fire in Terry
text:
TERRY, Miss. (AP) - Fire officials are trying to determine what sparked a large grass fire in Terry.
The fire Thursday afternoon charred 115 acres.
Firefighter Jason Whittington tells WAPT-TV ( http://bit.ly/1QOcxiD ) that it doesn't take but a second for a fire to spread, especially with it being so dry and high winds.
The Terry Fire Department said it doesn't know what sparked the fire but someone was bush-hogging in a pasture area off of Green Gable Road. Authorities said they evacuated three businesses near the blaze.
Firefighters built a fire wall to keep the flames contained in one area. Officials say smoke will continue to be seen because firefighters laid foam on the fire to keep it from spreading any further.
Information from: WAPT-TV, http://www.wapt.com
